HEADWORD: Observator
<hw>Ob"ser*va`tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>One who observes or takes notice.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Sir M. Hale.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who makes a remark.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Observatory</ent>⟦br⟧
